[779.138205, "o", "SSH_CONFIG(5)                  BSD File Formats Manual                 SSH_CONFIG(5)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mssh_config\u001b[0m — OpenSSH client configuration file\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n     ssh(1) obtains configuration data from the following sources in the following\u001b[m\r\n     order:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n           1.   command-line options\u001b[m\r\n           2.   user's configuration file (\u001b[4m~/.ssh/config\u001b[24m)\u001b[m\r\n           3.   system-wide configuration file (\u001b[4m/etc/ssh/ssh_config\u001b[24m)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[780.887465, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[780.887548, "o", "     For each parameter, the first obtained value will be used.  The configuration\u001b[m\r\n     files contain sections separated by \u001b[1mHost\u001b[0m specifications, and that section is\u001b[m\r\n     only applied for hosts that match one of the patterns given in the specifica‐\u001b[m\r\n     tion.  The matched host name is usually the one given on the command line (see\u001b[m\r\n     the \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m option for exceptions).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     Since the first obtained value for each parameter is used, more host-specific\u001b[m\r\n     declarations should be given near the beginning of the file, and general de‐\u001b[m\r\n     faults at the end.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     Note that the Debian \u001b[1mopenssh-client\u001b[0m package sets several options as standard in\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[4m/etc/ssh/ssh_config\u001b[24m which are not the default in ssh(1):\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 14 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[781.464186, "o", "\r\u001b[K           \u001b[1m•\u001b[0m   \u001b[1mInclude\u001b[0m \u001b[1m/etc/ssh/ssh_config.d/*.conf\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n           \u001b[1m•\u001b[0m   \u001b[1mSendEnv\u001b[0m LANG LC_*\u001b[m\r\n           \u001b[1m•\u001b[0m   \u001b[1mHashKnownHosts\u001b[0m yes\u001b[m\r\n           \u001b[1m•\u001b[0m   \u001b[1mGSSAPIAuthentication\u001b[0m yes\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[4m/etc/ssh/ssh_config.d/*.conf\u001b[24m files are included at the start of the system-wide\u001b[m\r\n     configuration file, so options set there will override those in\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[4m/etc/ssh/ssh_config.\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     The file contains keyword-argument pairs, one per line.  Lines starting with\u001b[m\r\n     ‘#’ and empty lines are interpreted as comments.  Arguments may optionally be\u001b[m\r\n     enclosed in double quotes (\") in order to represent arguments containing spa‐\u001b[m\r\n     ces.  Configuration options may be separated by whitespace or optional white‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 27 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[782.034139, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[782.034258, "o", "     space and exactly one ‘=’; the latter format is useful to avoid the need to\u001b[m\r\n     quote whitespace when specifying configuration options using the \u001b[1mssh\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m, and\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1msftp\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m option.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     The possible keywords and their meanings are as follows (note that keywords are\u001b[m\r\n     case-insensitive and arguments are case-sensitive):\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mHost\u001b[0m    Restricts the following declarations (up to the next \u001b[1mHost\u001b[0m or \u001b[1mMatch\u001b[0m key‐\u001b[m\r\n             word) to be only for those hosts that match one of the patterns given\u001b[m\r\n             after the keyword.  If more than one pattern is provided, they should\u001b[m\r\n             be separated by whitespace.  A single ‘*’ as a pattern can be used to\u001b[m\r\n             provide global defaults for all hosts.  The host is usually the\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[4mhostname\u001b[24m argument given on the command line (see the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 40 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[782.596297, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[782.596394, "o", "             \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m keyword for exceptions).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             A pattern entry may be negated by prefixing it with an exclamation mark\u001b[m\r\n             (‘!’).  If a negated entry is matched, then the \u001b[1mHost\u001b[0m entry is ignored,\u001b[m\r\n             regardless of whether any other patterns on the line match.  Negated\u001b[m\r\n             matches are therefore useful to provide exceptions for wildcard\u001b[m\r\n             matches.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             See \u001b[4mPATTERNS\u001b[24m for more information on patterns.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mMatch\u001b[0m   Restricts the following declarations (up to the next \u001b[1mHost\u001b[0m or \u001b[1mMatch\u001b[0m key‐\u001b[m\r\n             word) to be used only when the conditions following the \u001b[1mMatch\u001b[0m keyword\u001b[m\r\n             are satisfied.  Match conditions are specified using one or more crite‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 53 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[783.339369, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[783.339549, "o", "             ria or the single token \u001b[1mall\u001b[0m which always matches.  The available crite‐\u001b[m\r\n             ria keywords are: \u001b[1mcanonical\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mfinal\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mexec\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mhost\u001b[0m, \u001b[1moriginalhost\u001b[0m, \u001b[1muser\u001b[0m, and\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mlocaluser\u001b[0m.  The \u001b[1mall\u001b[0m criteria must appear alone or immediately after\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mcanonical\u001b[0m or \u001b[1mfinal\u001b[0m.  Other criteria may be combined arbitrarily.  All\u001b[m\r\n             criteria but \u001b[1mall\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mcanonical\u001b[0m, and \u001b[1mfinal\u001b[0m require an argument.  Criteria\u001b[m\r\n             may be negated by prepending an exclamation mark (‘!’).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             The \u001b[1mcanonical\u001b[0m keyword matches only when the configuration file is being\u001b[m\r\n             re-parsed after hostname canonicalization (see the \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             option).  This may be useful to specify conditions that work with\u001b[m\r\n             canonical host names only.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             The \u001b[1mfinal\u001b[0m keyword requests that the configur"]
[783.339566, "o", "ation be re-parsed (regard‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 66 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[784.082165, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[784.082192, "o", "             less of whether \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m is enabled), and matches only dur‐\u001b[m\r\n             ing this final pass.  If \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m is enabled, then\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mcanonical\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mfinal\u001b[0m match during the same pass.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             The \u001b[1mexec\u001b[0m keyword executes the specified command under the user's shell.\u001b[m\r\n             If the command returns a zero exit status then the condition is consid‐\u001b[m\r\n             ered true.  Commands containing whitespace characters must be quoted.\u001b[m\r\n             Arguments to \u001b[1mexec\u001b[0m accept the tokens described in the \u001b[4mTOKENS\u001b[24m section.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             The other keywords' criteria must be single entries or comma-separated\u001b[m\r\n             lists and may use the wildcard and negation operators described in the\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[4mPATTERNS\u001b[24m section.  The criteria for the \u001b[1mhost\u001b[0m keyword are matched\u001b[m\r\n             against the target hostname, after any substitution by the \u001b[1mHostname\u001b[0m or\u001b["]
[784.082199, "o", "m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 79 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[784.164036, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[784.164088, "o", "             \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m options.  The \u001b[1moriginalhost\u001b[0m keyword matches against\u001b[m\r\n             the hostname as it was specified on the command-line.  The \u001b[1muser\u001b[0m keyword\u001b[m\r\n             matches against the target username on the remote host.  The \u001b[1mlocaluser\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             keyword matches against the name of the local user running ssh(1) (this\u001b[m\r\n             keyword may be useful in system-wide \u001b[1mssh_config\u001b[0m files).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mAddKeysToAgent\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies whether keys should be automatically added to a running\u001b[m\r\n             ssh-agent(1).  If this option is set to \u001b[1myes\u001b[0m and a key is loaded from a\u001b[m\r\n             file, the key and its passphrase are added to the agent with the de‐\u001b[m\r\n             fault lifetime, as if by ssh-add(1).  If this option is set to \u001b[1mask\u001b[0m,\u001b[m\r\n             ssh(1) will require confirmation using the SSH_ASKPASS program before\u001b[m\r\n             adding a key (see ssh-add(1) for details).  If this option "]
[784.164097, "o", "is set to\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 92 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[785.484992, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K             \u001b[1mconfirm\u001b[0m, each use of the key must be confirmed, as if the \u001b[1m-c\u001b[0m option was\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 93 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[785.806734, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K             specified to ssh-add(1).  If this option is set to \u001b[1mno\u001b[0m, no keys are\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 94 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[791.784311, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[791.784411, "o", "             added to the agent.  Alternately, this option may be specified as a\u001b[m\r\n             time interval using the format described in the \u001b[4mTIME\u001b[24m \u001b[4mFORMATS\u001b[24m section of\u001b[m\r\n             sshd_config(5) to specify the key's lifetime in ssh-agent(1), after\u001b[m\r\n             which it will automatically be removed.  The argument must be \u001b[1mno\u001b[0m (the\u001b[m\r\n             default), \u001b[1myes\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mconfirm\u001b[0m (optionally followed by a time interval), \u001b[1mask\u001b[0m or\u001b[m\r\n             a time interval.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mAddressFamily\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies which address family to use when connecting.  Valid arguments\u001b[m\r\n             are \u001b[1many\u001b[0m (the default), \u001b[1minet\u001b[0m (use IPv4 only), or \u001b[1minet6\u001b[0m (use IPv6 only).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mBatchMode\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             If set to \u001b[1myes\u001b[0m, user interaction such as password prompts and host key\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 107 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[793.224465, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[793.224493, "o", "             confirmation requests will be disabled.  In addition, the\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mServerAliveInterval\u001b[0m option will be set to 300 seconds by default (De‐\u001b[m\r\n             bian-specific).  This option is useful in scripts and other batch jobs\u001b[m\r\n             where no user is present to interact with ssh(1), and where it is de‐\u001b[m\r\n             sirable to detect a broken network swiftly.  The argument must be \u001b[1myes\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             or \u001b[1mno\u001b[0m (the default).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mBindAddress\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Use the specified address on the local machine as the source address of\u001b[m\r\n             the connection.  Only useful on systems with more than one address.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mBindInterface\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Use the address of the specified interface on the local machine as the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 120 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[793.876642, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[793.876672, "o", "             source address of the connection.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mCanonicalDomains\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             When \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m is enabled, this option specifies the list of\u001b[m\r\n             domain suffixes in which to search for the specified destination host.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mCanonicalizeFallbackLocal\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies whether to fail with an error when hostname canonicalization\u001b[m\r\n             fails.  The default, \u001b[1myes\u001b[0m, will attempt to look up the unqualified host‐\u001b[m\r\n             name using the system resolver's search rules.  A value of \u001b[1mno\u001b[0m will\u001b[m\r\n             cause ssh(1) to fail instantly if \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m is enabled and\u001b[m\r\n             the target hostname cannot be found in any of the domains specified by\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mCanonicalDomains\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 133 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[794.446815, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[794.446877, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Controls whether explicit hostname canonicalization is performed.  The\u001b[m\r\n             default, \u001b[1mno\u001b[0m, is not to perform any name rewriting and let the system\u001b[m\r\n             resolver handle all hostname lookups.  If set to \u001b[1myes\u001b[0m then, for connec‐\u001b[m\r\n             tions that do not use a \u001b[1mProxyCommand\u001b[0m or \u001b[1mProxyJump\u001b[0m, ssh(1) will attempt\u001b[m\r\n             to canonicalize the hostname specified on the command line using the\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mCanonicalDomains\u001b[0m suffixes and \u001b[1mCanonicalizePermittedCNAMEs\u001b[0m rules.  If\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mCanonicalizeHostname\u001b[0m is set to \u001b[1malways\u001b[0m, then canonicalization is applied\u001b[m\r\n             to proxied connections too.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             If this option is enabled, then the configuration files are processed\u001b[m\r\n             again using the new target name to pick up any new configuration in\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 146 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[794.934259, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[794.93429, "o", "             matching \u001b[1mHost\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mMatch\u001b[0m stanzas.  A value of \u001b[1mnone\u001b[0m disables the use of a\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mProxyJump\u001b[0m host.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mCanonicalizeMaxDots\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies the maximum number of dot characters in a hostname before\u001b[m\r\n             canonicalization is disabled.  The default, 1, allows a single dot\u001b[m\r\n             (i.e. hostname.subdomain).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mCanonicalizePermittedCNAMEs\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies rules to determine whether CNAMEs should be followed when\u001b[m\r\n             canonicalizing hostnames.  The rules consist of one or more arguments\u001b[m\r\n             of \u001b[4msource_domain_list\u001b[24m:\u001b[4mtarget_domain_list\u001b[24m, where \u001b[4msource_domain_list\u001b[24m is a\u001b[m\r\n             pattern-list of domains that may follow CNAMEs in canonicalization, and\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 159 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[795.436185, "o", "\r\u001b[K             \u001b[4mtarget_domain_list\u001b[24m is a pattern-list of domains that they may resolve\u001b[m\r\n             to.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             For example, \"*.a.example.com:*.b.example.com,*.c.example.com\" will al‐\u001b[m\r\n             low hostnames matching \"*.a.example.com\" to be canonicalized to names\u001b[m\r\n             in the \"*.b.example.com\" or \"*.c.example.com\" domains.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             A single argument of \"none\" causes no CNAMEs to be considered for\u001b[m\r\n             canonicalization.  This is the default behaviour.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mCASignatureAlgorithms\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies which algorithms are allowed for signing of certificates by\u001b[m\r\n             certificate authorities (CAs).  The default is:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 172 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[795.992118, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[795.99229, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n                   ssh-ed25519,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,\u001b[m\r\n                   ecdsa-sha2-nistp384,ecdsa-sha2-nistp521,\u001b[m\r\n                   sk-ssh-ed25519@openssh.com,\u001b[m\r\n                   sk-ecdsa-sha2-nistp256@openssh.com,\u001b[m\r\n                   rsa-sha2-512,rsa-sha2-256\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             If the specified list begins with a ‘+’ character, then the specified\u001b[m\r\n             algorithms will be appended to the default set instead of replacing\u001b[m\r\n             them.  If the specified list begins with a ‘-’ character, then the\u001b[m\r\n             specified algorithms (including wildcards) will be removed from the de‐\u001b[m\r\n             fault set instead of replacing them.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 185 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
