[4933.077593, "o", "SCP(1)                       BSD General Commands Manual                      SCP(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m — OpenSSH secure file copy\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-346ABCOpqRrsTv\u001b[0m] [\u001b[1m-c\u001b[0m \u001b[4mcipher\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-D\u001b[0m \u001b[4msftp_server_path\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-F\u001b[0m \u001b[4mssh_config\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n         [\u001b[1m-i\u001b[0m \u001b[4midentity_file\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-J\u001b[0m \u001b[4mdestination\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-l\u001b[0m \u001b[4mlimit\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m \u001b[4mssh_option\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-P\u001b[0m \u001b[4mport\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n         [\u001b[1m-S\u001b[0m \u001b[4mprogram\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-X\u001b[0m \u001b[4msftp_option\u001b[24m] \u001b[4msource\u001b[24m \u001b[4m...\u001b[24m \u001b[4mtarget\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m copies files between hosts on a network.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m uses the SFTP protocol over a ssh(1) connection for data transfer, and uses\u001b[m\r\n     the same authentication and provides the same security as a login session.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m will ask for passwords or passphrases if they are needed for authentica‐\u001b[m\r\n     tion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7"]
[4933.077622, "o", "m Manual page scp(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4934.262169, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[4934.262307, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n     The \u001b[4msource\u001b[24m and \u001b[4mtarget\u001b[24m may be specified as a local pathname, a remote host with\u001b[m\r\n     optional path in the form [user@]host:[path], or a URI in the form\u001b[m\r\n     scp://[user@]host[:port][/path].  Local file names can be made explicit using\u001b[m\r\n     absolute or relative pathnames to avoid \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m treating file names containing ‘:’\u001b[m\r\n     as host specifiers.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     When copying between two remote hosts, if the URI format is used, a \u001b[4mport\u001b[24m cannot\u001b[m\r\n     be specified on the \u001b[4mtarget\u001b[24m if the \u001b[1m-R\u001b[0m option is used.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     The options are as follows:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-3\u001b[0m      Copies between two remote hosts are transferred through the local host.\u001b[m\r\n             Without this option the data is copied directly between the two remote\u001b[m\r\n             hosts.  Note that, when using the legacy SCP protocol (via the \u001b[1m-O\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             flag), this option selects batch mode for the second host as \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m cannot\u001b[m\r\n             ask fo"]
[4934.262322, "o", "r passwords or passphrases for both hosts.  This mode is the de‐\u001b[m\r\n             fault.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 19 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4935.086509, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[4935.086552, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-4\u001b[0m      Forces \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m to use IPv4 addresses only.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-6\u001b[0m      Forces \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m to use IPv6 addresses only.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-A\u001b[0m      Allows forwarding of ssh-agent(1) to the remote system.  The default is\u001b[m\r\n             not to forward an authentication agent.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-B\u001b[0m      Selects batch mode (prevents asking for passwords or passphrases).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n"]
[4935.086626, "o", "     \u001b[1m-C\u001b[0m      Compression enable.  Passes the \u001b[1m-C\u001b[0m flag to ssh(1) to enable compres‐\u001b[m\r\n             sion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-c\u001b[0m \u001b[4mcipher\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Selects the cipher to use for encrypting the data transfer.  This op‐\u001b[m\r\n             tion is directly passed to ssh(1).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-D\u001b[0m \u001b[4msftp_server_path\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 37 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4936.429961, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[4936.4301, "o", "             Connect directly to a local SFTP server program rather than a remote\u001b[m\r\n             one via ssh(1).  This option may be useful in debugging the client and\u001b[m\r\n             server.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-F\u001b[0m \u001b[4mssh_config\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies an alternative per-user configuration file for \u001b[1mssh\u001b[0m.  This op‐\u001b[m\r\n             tion is directly passed to ssh(1).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-i\u001b[0m \u001b[4midentity_file\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Selects the file from which the identity (private key) for public key\u001b[m\r\n             authentication is read.  This option is directly passed to ssh(1).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-J\u001b[0m \u001b[4mdestination\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Connect to the target host by first making an \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m connection to the\u001b[m\r\n             jump host described by \u001b[4mdestination\u001b[24m and then establishing a TCP forward‐\u001b[m\r\n             ing to the ultimate destination from there.  Multiple jump hops may be\u001b[m\r\n             specified separated by comma characters.  This is a shortcut to specif"]
[4936.430122, "o", "y\u001b[m\r\n             a \u001b[1mProxyJump\u001b[0m configuration directive.  This option is directly passed to\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 55 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4937.07473, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[4937.074753, "o", "             ssh(1).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-l\u001b[0m \u001b[4mlimit\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Limits the used bandwidth, specified in Kbit/s.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-O\u001b[0m      Use the legacy SCP protocol for file transfers instead of the SFTP pro‐\u001b[m\r\n"]
[4937.074867, "o", "             tocol.  Forcing the use of the SCP protocol may be necessary for\u001b[m\r\n             servers that do not implement SFTP, for backwards-compatibility for\u001b[m\r\n             particular filename wildcard patterns and for expanding paths with a\u001b[m\r\n             ‘~’ prefix for older SFTP servers.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m \u001b[4mssh_option\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Can be used to pass options to \u001b[1mssh\u001b[0m in the format used in ssh_config(5).\u001b[m\r\n             This is useful for specifying options for which there is no separate\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mscp\u001b[0m command-line flag.  For full details of the options listed below,\u001b[m\r\n             and their possible values, see ssh_config(5).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n                   AddressFamily\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 73 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4938.109942, "o", "\r\u001b[K                   BatchMode\u001b[m\r\n                   BindAddress\u001b[m\r\n                   BindInterface\u001b[m\r\n                   CanonicalDomains\u001b[m\r\n                   CanonicalizeFallbackLocal\u001b[m\r\n                   CanonicalizeHostname\u001b[m\r\n                   CanonicalizeMaxDots\u001b[m\r\n                   CanonicalizePermittedCNAMEs\u001b[m\r\n                   CASignatureAlgorithms\u001b[m\r\n                   CertificateFile\u001b[m\r\n                   CheckHostIP\u001b[m\r\n                   Ciphers\u001b[m\r\n                   Compression\u001b[m\r\n                   ConnectionAttempts\u001b[m\r\n                   ConnectTimeout\u001b[m\r\n                   ControlMaster\u001b[m\r\n                   ControlPath\u001b[m\r\n                   ControlPersist\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 91 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4938.724688, "o", "\r\u001b[K                   GlobalKnownHostsFile\u001b[m\r\n                   GSSAPIAuthentication\u001b[m\r\n                   GSSAPIDelegateCredentials\u001b[m\r\n                   HashKnownHosts\u001b[m\r\n                   Host\u001b[m\r\n                   HostbasedAcceptedAlgorithms\u001b[m\r\n                   HostbasedAuthentication\u001b[m\r\n                   HostKeyAlgorithms\u001b[m\r\n                   HostKeyAlias\u001b[m\r\n                   Hostname\u001b[m\r\n                   IdentitiesOnly\u001b[m\r\n                   IdentityAgent\u001b[m\r\n                   IdentityFile\u001b[m\r\n                   IPQoS\u001b[m\r\n                   KbdInteractiveAuthentication\u001b[m\r\n                   KbdInteractiveDevices\u001b[m\r\n                   KexAlgorithms\u001b[m\r\n                   KnownHostsCommand\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 109 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4939.046653, "o", "\r\u001b[K                   LogLevel\u001b[m\r\n                   MACs\u001b[m\r\n                   NoHostAuthenticationForLocalhost\u001b[m\r\n                   NumberOfPasswordPrompts\u001b[m\r\n                   PasswordAuthentication\u001b[m\r\n                   PKCS11Provider\u001b[m\r\n                   Port\u001b[m\r\n                   PreferredAuthentications\u001b[m\r\n                   ProxyCommand\u001b[m\r\n                   ProxyJump\u001b[m\r\n                   PubkeyAcceptedAlgorithms\u001b[m\r\n                   PubkeyAuthentication\u001b[m\r\n                   RekeyLimit\u001b[m\r\n                   RequiredRSASize\u001b[m\r\n                   SendEnv\u001b[m\r\n                   ServerAliveInterval\u001b[m\r\n                   ServerAliveCountMax\u001b[m\r\n                   SetEnv\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 127 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4939.332006, "o", "\r\u001b[K                   StrictHostKeyChecking\u001b[m\r\n                   TCPKeepAlive\u001b[m\r\n                   UpdateHostKeys\u001b[m\r\n                   User\u001b[m\r\n                   UserKnownHostsFile\u001b[m\r\n                   VerifyHostKeyDNS\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-P\u001b[0m \u001b[4mport\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies the port to connect to on the remote host.  Note that this\u001b[m\r\n             option is written with a capital ‘P’, because \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m is already reserved\u001b[m\r\n             for preserving the times and mode bits of the file.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m      Preserves modification times, access times, and file mode bits from the\u001b[m\r\n             source file.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-q\u001b[0m      Quiet mode: disables the progress meter as well as warning and diagnos‐\u001b[m\r\n             tic messages from ssh(1).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page scp(1) line 145 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4951.67012, "o", "\r\u001b[K\u001b[?1l\u001b>\u001b[?1049l\u001b[23;0;0t"]
[4951.676283, "o", "\u001b[?2004h\u001b[94mDEVOPS25/lektion5\r\r\n\u001b(B\u001b[m$ "]
